main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in the sky over Crane, Indiana on 17 September 1956.
interesting points: The objects were seen for approximately 20 minutes, traveling at high speed and changing colors from white to red to green., Witnesses described the objects as flying at an altitude of 2000 to 3000 feet without any sound or vapor trails., A member of the Depot Fire Department attempted to get a closer look at the objects as they maneuvered in the sky., The sighting was concluded to be unknown by the observing officer, suggesting they could have been balloons., The report compiles multiple witness accounts corroborating the observation of the objects.
witness description: witnesses included residents from Bloomfield, Indiana, including a couple and individuals associated with local businesses.
